It sounds to me as though using PERMANOVA may be preferable. See, for example, https://doi.org/10.1002/9781118445112.stat07841 <https://doi.org/10.1002/9781118445112.stat07841>. The R package, vegan, can implement this technique. R: Permutational Multivariate Analysis of Variance Using Distance ...cc.oulu.fi/~jarioksa/softhelp/vegan/html/adonis.html <https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=1&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=2ahUKEwjSrbrKw_DgAhWFtZ4KHd8xBuMQFjAAegQIChAB&url=http%3A%2F%2Fcc.oulu.fi%2F~jarioksa%2Fsofthelp%2Fvegan%2Fhtml%2Fadonis.html&usg=AOvVaw1iRL1qmIXZ3jRobbXfkvyk>


